miscConds.notes: Maintain full time work, school or combination of the two.
Commit no further criminal acts during the period of this agreement.

Defendant shall comply with any and all rules of probation in a timely fashion and successfully complete any term of probation ordered as a part of this case. Defendant shall provide a copy of this agreement, along with the Criminal Complaint, to any counselor and sign any and all releases necessary to allow the counselor (or agency) to report compliance or lack thereof to the District Attorney's Office. Any assessments done without this agreement and the Criminal Complaint(s) being supplied to the counselor will be considered violations of this agreement and not be accepted.  This agreement may be revoked or the defendant may have to complete a new assessment.

timeConds.notes: Defendant shall perform 150 hours of uncompensated community service, providing proof of such community service to the Door County District Attorney's office at least thirty (30) days before the expiration of this agreement.
